<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1407] Typo in Python socket server causes Thrift to fail when we enable a global socket timout</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1407</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a typo in thrift.transport.TSocket.TServerSocket: instead of &quot;settimeout&quot;, we have &quot;set_timeout&quot;. This causes the code to not work properly when we enable a global socket timeout in Python, using &quot;socket.settimeout(30)&quot;. Because of the typo, the Python Thrift server will fail to change it&apos;s socket back to a non-timing out mode, and the listen call will fail after the timeout passes.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
